      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elasto-plastic material model with isotropic hardening validated for Ti-6Al-4V and UHMWPE at quasi-static loading rates. Contact mechanics formulation appropriate for screw-rod interface.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model calibrated from tensile coupon data for Ti-6Al-4V (n=6 coupons per batch, two batches) and UHMWPE rod (n=6 per batch). Augmented Lagrangian contact formulation used for screw-rod and rod-vertebral body block interfaces. Model form consistent with prior published FEA studies of F1717 constructs. Gradation 3 achieved."
