      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the clinical and regulatory decision being supported.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness relates to load sharing and adjacent segment effects; yield force is the primary structural integrity indicator; force at 40 mm displacement captures post-yield energy absorption relevant to fracture risk. All three QoIs are cited in FDA guidance for pedicle screw 510(k) submissions and directly inform the substantial equivalence determination. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
