      "rationale": "Validation testing uses the identical screw-rod construct geometry and ASTM F1717 protocol as the COU. Two independent laboratories provide geographic and equipment diversity. The only deviation from clinical conditions is the use of rigid vertebral body blocks rather than cadaveric bone, which is standard practice for F1717 and accepted by FDA for this device class. Gradation 3 achieved."
